            <p>Having recently completed the Le Wagon Web Developer 10-week full-time Bootcamp in Amsterdam, I’m now looking for a full-stack developer role within the Netherlands. The full-stack role appeals to me for two reasons: 1) the breadth of the role; learning the skillset for both front and back-end is as exciting as it is daunting (I think both are needed when starting a new journey), and 2) combining functionality and creativity; this is something I have always done and can see clear similarities within the full-stack job function. I have worked with Ruby, Ruby on Rails, SQL, JSON, HTML, CSS, JavaScript, as well as OOP and MVC structures.<br><br>These topics have been covered extensively within the Le Wagon Bootcamp and I have also studied these subjects online through CodeCademy. However, I’m very aware that this is only the beginning and I am very much looking forward to learning more about these (and other) languages/methodologies in my future career.<br><br></p>
